About Chateau Village
55+ Mobile Home Community Living in Sunny West Coast Florida!
Located in the heart of Bradenton, Chateau Village outshines all the surrounding parks. Chateau Village is an age-restricted community that features over 275 lots on the beautiful West Coast of Florida. Our friendly residents are active in the community and enjoy participating in social events.
Surrounded by beautiful beaches, lakes, gardens, and wildlife preserves, residents and vacationers alike have the choice of many area attractions to explore.
Our lush green yards are evidence of a community where residents exhibit great pride. With 40 beautiful acres, this 55+ community is a wonderful place to call home.
Robinson Preserve
Nationally recognized as the area’s #1 family activity, the Robinson Preserve provides fun for the entire family. The preserve consists of 682 acres that is a mix of mangroves and tidal marsh.
Beaches
Florida’s warm, sandy west coast beaches are just a short drive away.
Area Golf
Semi-private and Municipal Golf Clubs, including IMG Academy Golf Club, Timber Creek Golf Club and River Run Golf Links.
Bradenton Riverwalk
Take a stroll along the 1.5 mile Riverwalk that overlooks the Manatee River and features an amphitheater, beach volleyball, a skate park and much more!
Myakka River State Park
Myakka River flows through a vast expanse of unspoiled wetlands, prairies and pinelands that make up Myakka River State Park. Boating, fishing, canoeing and kayaking are popular activities here.
Sporting Events
Need a break from endless relaxation? Professional sporting events up and down the coast will get your adrenaline pumping!
